data.name: THAI WAH
data.description: THAI WAH is the leader in starch-related solutions in Asia, serving customers in more than 30 countries with the best tapioca, mung bean, rice and other starch and food related products, as well as innovative solutions for clean label, healthy solutions and functional solutions. The company’s core business is divided into tree main categories: the manufacture of tapioca products, vermicelli and noodle products, and bioplastic from tapioca based for local and international distribution. THAI WAH produces premium quality products to satisfy our customers, and is committed to corporate social responsibility (CSR) as a guideline to doing business.

data.name: ROSEBRAND CASSTEX 19
data.description: ROSEBRAND CASSTEX 19 is a versatile ingredient that enhances the texture and consistency of your culinary creations. This high-quality modified tapioca starch is available in both powder and solid forms, offering convenience and flexibility in your food preparation. With its natural origin derived from tapioca plants, ROSEBRAND CASSTEX 19 provides improved thickness, allowing you to achieve the desired texture in your savory and bakery products. Its texturizing properties make it a valuable addition to your recipes, ensuring a satisfying mouthfeel. Utilize the benefits of this modified tapioca starch to elevate the quality of your dishes, whether you're baking delicious pastries or creating savory culinary delights.

data.name: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup DE 27
data.description: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup DE 27 is a premium organic sweetener perfect for a wide range of food applications. This tapioca syrup falls under the Sweeteners & Syrups product family in the Taste & Flavor category of food ingredients. It caters to markets such as bakery, confectionery, desserts & fruit preparations, beverage (juice & juice drinks), dairy, and food processing & packaging. With its nutritive sweetener function and delightful sweet taste, it enhances the flavor profile of your products. ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup DE 27 is made from plant-origin ingredients, ensuring its natural authenticity. It comes in a convenient liquid form, available in drums, totes (IBC), and tanks. This organic tapioca syrup meets stringent certifications and compliance standards, including FSSC 22000, Halal, Kosher, and GMP, guaranteeing its quality and reliability.

data.name: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup (GL40A)
data.description: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup (GL40A) is a premium sweetener that brings a touch of natural sweetness to your culinary creations. This tapioca syrup falls under the Sweeteners & Syrups product category, making it an essential ingredient in various food applications. It caters to markets such as bakery, confectionery, desserts & fruit preparations, beverage (juice & juice drinks), dairy, and food processing & packaging. With its nutritive sweetener function, it enhances the taste profile of your food products. Made from plant-origin ingredients, this organic tapioca syrup maintains its natural authenticity. It comes in a convenient liquid form, packaged in drums, totes (IBC), and tanks for easy availability. Enjoy the benefits of this organic sweetener with its sweet taste and certifications, including being Non-GMO, Halal, Kosher, and GMP compliant.

content_blocks.html:
ROSECO series which is the unique type of thermoplastic starch resin, derived from Tapioca starch. It can be used in various applications such as organic waste bags, shopping bags, thermoform tray, cutlery, agricultural bio mulch film, consumer goods, etc.

ROSECO series will help you to:

  • Increase the renewable content of your products more than 50%
  • Reduce your carbon footprint and "End of life" waste solution
  • Provide cost saving formulation to increase market potential
  • Solution for conventional application processes blown and cast film, injection

 

Thermoplastic Starch ROSECO TPS

 

  • Affordable solution
  • Renewable feedstock
  • Bio-content > 90% incease renewable
  • Higher elongation Vs corn based
  • Suitable for flexible packaging
  • Application due to its flexibility
  • Home compostable within 60 days


Bio-Compound From ROSECO TPS

 

  • High performance and thin film applications
  • Compatible with advance composites/good
  • Processibility and product stability
  • Sustainable compound for end-of-life application
  • Home/industrial compostable

Our tapioca-based TPS is derived from renewable feedstock with >90% bio content and better mechanical properties suitable for flexible packaging application of mulch film, bags and other blown film applications. Our first generation of TPS compounds, suitable for end-of-life applications thermo forming, injection molding and extrusion, are a unique blend of high performing biodegradable feedstock that are both industrial and home compostable.  

Increase the sustainability of the plastic products with ROSECO series, tapioca based functional thermoplastic biopolymers. It is a great option to replace 30-50% of petroleum based or compostable polymer resins in blown film, injection molding and casting application with the goal of biodegradability and composability. The blend and compound of thermoplastic starch with all bio-polymers and additives are recently globally developed for greater performance in commercial use.

ROSECO TPS is good compatible with biopolymers to produce compostable compounds, suitable for end-of-life applications blown and cast films, thermoforming, injection molding and extrusion, are unique blend of high performing biodegradable feedstock that are both industrial and home compostable.

 

Disintegration test of ROSECO Bio-compost compound (according to ISO 16929)
